# üî• Firebase Integration - NYA BLO

## ‚úÖ Configuration Compl√®te

Firebase est maintenant **100% configur√©** pour NYA BLO avec:

- ‚úÖ **Authentication** (Email/Password + Google)
- ‚úÖ **Firestore Database** (NoSQL cloud)
- ‚úÖ **Storage** (Files & Images)  
- ‚úÖ **Analytics** (Tracking √©v√©nements)

---

## üì¶ Fichiers Cr√©√©s

| Fichier | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `lib/firebase/config.ts` | Configuration principale + initialisation |
| `lib/firebase/firestore.ts` | CRUD operations + helpers m√©tier |
| `lib/firebase/analytics.ts` | Tracking √©v√©nements utilisateurs |
| `hooks/useAuth.ts` | Hook React pour authentification |
| `.env.local.example` | Template variables d'environnement |

---

## üîê Authentication

### Utilisation du Hook

```typescript
import { useAuth } from '@/hooks/useAuth';

function MyComponent() {
    const { user, loading, signIn, signUp, signInWithGoogle, signOut } = useAuth();

    // Sign up
    await signUp('user@example.com', 'password123');

    // Sign in
    await signIn('user@example.com', 'password123');

    // Google sign in
    await signInWithGoogle();

    // Sign out
    await signOut();

    if (loading) return <div>Loading...</div>;
    if (!user) return <div>Not logged in</div>;

    return <div>Welcome {user.email}</div>;
}
```

---

## üìä Firestore Database

### Collections Disponibles

```typescript
import { userService, orderService, cvService } from '@/lib/firebase/firestore';

// Users
await userService.get(userId);
await userService.create(userId, { name: 'John', email: 'john@nya-blo.com' });
await userService.update(userId, { premium: true });

// Orders
await orderService.getByUser(userId);
await orderService.create({
    userId,
    items: [...],
    total: 50000,
});

// CVs
await cvService.getByUser(userId);
await cvService.save(cvId, cvData);
```

### Generic CRUD

```typescript
import { 
    getDocument, 
    getDocuments, 
    setDocument, 
    updateDocument, 
    deleteDocument 
} from '@/lib/firebase/firestore';

// Get single document
const user = await getDocument('users', userId);

// Get multiple documents with filters
import { where, orderBy } from 'firebase/firestore';
const orders = await getDocuments('orders', [
    where('userId', '==', userId),
    orderBy('createdAt', 'desc')
]);

// Create/update
await setDocument('users', userId, { name: 'Alice' });

// Update
await updateDocument('users', userId, { premium: true });

// Delete
await deleteDocument('users', userId);
```

